---
name: scljet-sql-strfunc
description: SclJet SQL string functions — SUBSTR (1-based, negative-from-end), TRIM/LTRIM/RTRIM, REPLACE; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL string functions

`SUBSTR(s, y[, z])` (1-based; `y<0` counts from the right; `z` clamps to the string), `TRIM`/`LTRIM`/
`RTRIM` (default trims spaces, optional char set), and `REPLACE(s, from, to)` (all non-overlapping
occurrences). They read from columns, compose with the other functions and `||`, and work in `WHERE`.
Every result is byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified
out-of-band), including the significant leading/trailing spaces of LTRIM/RTRIM; locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "items", "CREATE TABLE items(id INTEGER, code TEXT, label TEXT)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("  Widget  "), SqlText("A-B-C")),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("gadget"), SqlText("x_y_z")),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("Gizmo Pro"), SqlText("p-q")))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, TRIM(code) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, LENGTH(TRIM(code)) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, SUBSTR(label, 1, 3) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, SUBSTR(label, -3) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, REPLACE(label, '-', '+') FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, LTRIM(code) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id, RTRIM(code) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT UPPER(TRIM(code)) || '#' || SUBSTR(label, 1, 1) FROM items")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM items WHERE TRIM(code) = 'gadget'")
```
